[Washoe County, with an estimated population of 465 735 residents in 2018, is located in the northwestern portion of the US state of Nevada; there are 2 incorporated cities within the county, Reno and Sparks, which are 4 miles apart (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Washoe_County,_Nevada). Bishop Manogue Catholic High School is a Catholic high school in Reno, Nevada (https://www.bishopmanogue.org). A map showing the location of Reno and Sparks can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Reno,+Nevada/Sparks,+Nevada. - Mod.ML]

