[4] Missouri (Jefferson County)
Date: 4 Nov 2019
Source: Fox2 Now [edited]
https://fox2now.com/2019/11/04/fifteen-students-test-positive-for-whooping-cough-at-festus-schools/


A Jefferson County school district has an outbreak of whooping cough. So far, more than a dozen cases have been reported.

Pertussis or whooping cough began to appear at the Festus High School and Intermediate School around mid-October [2019]. District officials say 59 students have reported symptoms: 15 have tested positive for whooping cough, while 22 tested negative, and 22 were waiting for results. 14 of the students attend the high school and one student at the intermediate school.

The district was asked whether unvaccinated students were the cause of the outbreak. The district says that's not the case. Less than half a percent of the student population is unvaccinated. None of those who tested positive to pertussis displayed symptoms.

