[5] Ohio (Warren County)
Date: Thu 7 Nov 2019
Source: Dayton247 Now [edited]
https://dayton247now.com/news/local/whooping-cough-cases-confirmed-at-3-springboro-schools


Springboro Schools has sent out a warning to parents, confirming that cases of pertussis or whooping have now been found at the high school, the junior high, and at Springboro Intermediate. Two separate alerts have gone out to parents after cases were 1st reported. Those alerts only involved the high school.

If a child is experiencing persistent cough or if you have any questions or concerns, contact a physician. Whooping cough is a vaccine-preventable disease. If your child is not up to date, you can contact the Warren County Health Department for assistance at 513-695-2097.

[Byline: Rebeckah Chenoweth]

